President Obama has declared a major disaster in Montana and authorized federal aid to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts following a wildfire that occurred between June 25 and July 10, 2012. The funding will be available for emergency work, facility repair or replacement, and hazard mitigation measures in Powder River and Rosebud Counties and the Northern Cheyenne Indian Reservation. Thomas J. McCool has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area.